        "No job processing duration histogram — cannot detect slowdowns or confirm visibility timeout safety",
        "No duplicate processing counter — silent duplicates will go unnoticed",
        "No message age metric (time from enqueue to dequeue) — SLA violations invisible",
        "No in-flight message count — cannot assess worker saturation",
        "No error breakdown by type (corrupt image, timeout, OOM, etc.)"
      ]
    },
    "tracing": {
      "coverage": "No mention of distributed tracing",
      "gaps": [
        "No trace ID propagation from upstream producer to worker — cannot correlate a job to the request that created it",
        "No span for individual image processing steps (download, transform, upload)"
      ]
    },
    "debugging_capability": "Insufficient. At 3am when the queue has 50,000 messages backed up, the on-call engineer will see jobs_processed_total incrementing normally and /health returning 200. They will have NO visibility into the growing backlog, no way to identify poison messages, and no way to determine if messages are being processed twice."
